  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-PROV-01 orphan chain node)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package contains a broken provenance chain: an intermediate ValidationResult node (synth/validation/orphan-intermediate) is reachable from the Claim via prov:wasDerivedFrom but carries no upstream prov:wasDerivedFrom, prov:wasGeneratedBy, or prov:used edge, and is not marked uofa:isFoundationalEvidence:true, causing a dead-end in the provenance graph (W-PROV-01).",
